test_if_sublist_product_equals_number:
assert 3249 == 57
 +  where 3249 = <built-in function prod>([1, 3, 19, 57])
 +    where <built-in function prod> = math.prod
test_presence_of_duplicates_in_result:
assert (3 == 3 and 3 == 3 and 0 == 3)
 +  where 3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x707adecd8ac0>([57])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x707adecd8ac0> = [[1, 57], [1, 57, 1, 57], [1, 57, 1, 57, 1, 57], [57], [57, 1, 57], [57, 1, 57, 1, 57], ...].count
 +  and   3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x707adecd8ac0>([1, 57])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x707adecd8ac0> = [[1, 57], [1, 57, 1, 57], [1, 57, 1, 57, 1, 57], [57], [57, 1, 57], [57, 1, 57, 1, 57], ...].count
 +  and   0 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x707adecd8ac0>([57, 1])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x707adecd8ac0> = [[1, 57], [1, 57, 1, 57], [1, 57, 1, 57, 1, 57], [57], [57, 1, 57], [57, 1, 57, 1, 57], ...].count
